[
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.1",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Paul, a prisoner of Jesus Christ, and Timothy {our} brother, unto Philemon our dearly beloved, and fellowlabourer,",
    "hash": "3e1957f2b8ac7203a8cc6ae665405ab2eeb28742bdb9d4a3b35bafed30253b03"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.2",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "And to {our} beloved Apphia, and Archippus our fellowsoldier, and to the church in thy house:",
    "hash": "58e619da509363b9d899733bebd8c46eb0e7d7bd990c5cb673876e35e68d4fb2"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.3",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.",
    "hash": "4c98bc63abc4c462c3f7dfcfe5d15f67c901721b6a24634e7a224a6750c2da56"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.4",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "I thank my God, making mention of thee always in my prayers,",
    "hash": "cbcb0f3c8ba68c02338ffbb6f4d5f9b1be4e208b76437a25bb35a3f34fbe1259"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.5",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Hearing of thy love and faith, which thou hast toward the Lord Jesus, and toward all saints;",
    "hash": "abcc1c3d4c8a7e4e45156436bfc863ad5445270533f8aca818163865d6e4e951"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.6",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "That the communication of thy faith may become effectual by the acknowledging of every good thing which is in you in Christ Jesus.",
    "hash": "520f9cf97bb431060c9729dde92961ad6bafbd5ce4db714a183fde74bf10400d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.7",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "For we have great joy and consolation in thy love, because the bowels of the saints are refreshed by thee, brother.",
    "hash": "01a124e5ecb6ed8f1152d88efcfdadbd1940564ac49e42315f568bb30c122656"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.8",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Wherefore, though I might be much bold in Christ to enjoin thee that which is convenient,",
    "hash": "d8e27626dce7cac96a12af14f1f335f6fae8adf5e03865a213d32f428827b3fd"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.9",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Yet for love's sake I rather beseech {thee}, being such an one as Paul the aged, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.",
    "hash": "68d0bfac992aff3772444d27e49a2b79b5850ce3be2eaf113e3939ca7f2ede86"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.10",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "I beseech thee for my son Onesimus, whom I have begotten in my bonds:",
    "hash": "b78d169741d2f0157341749ad42340119dee2fd2854240d7528d99a03774acf7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.11",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Which in time past was to thee unprofitable, but now profitable to thee and to me:",
    "hash": "f4665b1c557f55ca911d9989a12f905c975c67fa1ce4a1eabe868559b3e7659e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.12",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Whom I have sent again: thou therefore receive him, that is, mine own bowels:",
    "hash": "8293150aa44f860340eade5c6558dcaebfd8a5bbbeefaf29af6d13b7ac9f6f15"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.13",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Whom I would have retained with me, that in thy stead he might have ministered unto me in the bonds of the gospel:",
    "hash": "f38433884ff279637ccd7b7ba13f0cc4bb905bf47c0b72aefa884b631893d9f7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.14",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "But without thy mind would I do nothing; that thy benefit should not be as it were of necessity, but willingly.",
    "hash": "ec117e3d1d1c67a5d992b4f38720e5b233b9f218637347485be5904775fc3a6c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.15",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "For perhaps he therefore departed for a season, that thou shouldest receive him for ever;",
    "hash": "14555ffa76b59e1c580a0d235175e507b19922125dfbf1c229c46a1d6eb1848b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.16",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Not now as a servant, but above a servant, a brother beloved, specially to me, but how much more unto thee, both in the flesh, and in the Lord?",
    "hash": "3e122ccbb5922a1442c4c79c2b7547db5a57264322ef4ba8e75305cc6e0e3132"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.17",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "If thou count me therefore a partner, receive him as myself.",
    "hash": "0511c551fac295eca789beeea660488456a5a23c59508b7454c310a945743f49"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.18",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "If he hath wronged thee, or oweth {thee} ought, put that on mine account;",
    "hash": "4f706df7d12fd6ed6bb2cd021395f8aa40083313fec745684ec009fd1ae9ac8f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.19",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "I Paul have written {it} with mine own hand, I will repay {it}: albeit I do not say to thee how thou owest unto me even thine own self besides.",
    "hash": "e07cb2501be284c3a8fbb3653bc474b0b6a15d847b24f18004ec245c54f62385"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.20",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Yea, brother, let me have joy of thee in the Lord: refresh my bowels in the Lord.",
    "hash": "785e24f1231fc184eb653e25883e825baa07cf39af9627c4a2ebfc272b4d5846"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.21",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Having confidence in thy obedience I wrote unto thee, knowing that thou wilt also do more than I say.",
    "hash": "ad43297664c6c28d9f5a12e01265dec1864244ab5088943b6cc9a7163d77000d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.22",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "But withal prepare me also a lodging: for I trust that through your prayers I shall be given unto you.",
    "hash": "a9211097904d8ab94c82428b02df273293e06c118c341a0a6440301dae7da701"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.23",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "There salute thee Epaphras, my fellowprisoner in Christ Jesus;",
    "hash": "52933722233280cfb707db72533c0589945e6b7f8d4172c95efbcb5dcb9d3840"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.24",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Marcus, Aristarchus, Demas, Lucas, my fellowlabourers.",
    "hash": "ad3b2b6636b8909dcd1b1daa478986ab43ce50b5fce6675642c5c2c5c1672bf5"
  },
  {
    "id": "PHM.1.25",
    "book": "Philemon",
    "bookNum": 57,
    "bookAbbrev": "PHM",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ {be} with your spirit. Amen. «{Written from Rome to Philemon, by Onesimus a servant.}»",
    "hash": "e11f20c615dfd573ce9d917647b20535fea671688589b7c2b3bff1fd3818f32e"
  }
]